1
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,400
{\an8}Saifah, help me!

2
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:02,080
{\an8}- There's a fire! Come on,come here!
- Help! Please help my brother!

3
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:03,960
{\an8}No! Let go of me!

4
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,080
{\an8}- No, Mr. Thee!
- Do you have any idea

5
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:08,479
{\an8}how much we had to suffer?

6
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:10,280
{\an8}How could you leave your own kids?!

7
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,000
{\an8}- Mr. Thee!
- How could you?!

8
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:14,520
{\an8}How about Tawan, honey? Did he come too?

9
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:17,640
{\an8}Is your brother here too? Is he?

10
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:19,240
{\an8}Where is he?

11
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:21,040
{\an8}That's unrelated, though.

12
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,080
{\an8}Even though I've met my mom,

13
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:27,800
{\an8}I never thought of leaving you.

14
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:28,760
{\an8}No!

15
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:31,960
{\an8}You have no choice
but to be someone I've created,

16
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:35,720
{\an8}and I'm the only mother you can have.

17
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,320
Mr. Thee,

18
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:44,560
how's Ms. Narin doing?

19
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,560
She's still in the OR.

20
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:54,160
Doctor, how is my mother?

21
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,720
The surgery went smoothly.

22
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:58,320
I'm transferring her to the ICU,

23
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:01,640
so we can closely monitor her condition
for a day or two.

24
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:04,320
If everything looks good,
she can be transferred to a room,

25
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,640
so please don't worry.

26
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:08,440
Okay. Thank you, Doctor.

27
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:10,840
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

28
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,640
<i>I know my mother ended our contract.</i>

29
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:32,720
Let's not discuss it yet, Mr. Thee.

30
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:36,000
Don't worry, Mr. Thee.

31
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:38,160
Mr. Pat and I will handle it.

32
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:42,080
Actually, I was going to tell you
that my mother had no right to do it.

33
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:45,600
Why not?

34
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:51,680
Why wouldn't I be able to end it?

35
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:53,360
We're the employer here.

36
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:03,760
You can end it,
but if you do it without cause,

37
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:06,640
The One must pay
50% of the contract's value

38
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:09,440
as severance pay to A Round Trip Travel.

39
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:12,480
Mr. Thee added this condition
to the contract.

40
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:16,240
Our legal team just checked the details
and notified me about it.

41
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:23,040
Don't tell me,
Thee's planned this from the start.

42
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,200
So, how much do you know
about Thee's mother?

43
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:31,440
I never knew
he was looking for his mother.

44
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:34,240
He never told me before.

45
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:41,760
So Narin is actually his real mother.

46
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:46,480
So this is why he bought her business.

47
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:49,400
Yes.

48
00:04:52,280 --> 00:04:54,040
Which means that

49
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:58,360
The One holds shares
in Narin Beach Resort.

50
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:02,440
What are you planning to do, Mrs. Anna?

51
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:08,880
Since Thee's refusing to do
what I want him to,

52
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,720
I'll have to handle it my way.

53
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:22,320
I heard that Mrs. Anna

54
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:25,440
removed you as the CEO at TJ Group.

55
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,960
I'm sorry for causing you trouble.

56
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:30,680
It's got nothing to do with you.

57
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:35,040
It's just because Mom…

58
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,200
I mean, Mrs. Anna…

59
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:39,920
Just call her what you used to.

60
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,080
Okay.

61
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:47,920
Mom's probably mad at me
for not marrying Bell.

62
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:50,600
You mean Ms. Bella,

63
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:54,000
the girl who came with Mrs. Anna
when we had that party at the hotel?

64
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:55,400
Yes.

65
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:58,280
Bell and I have known each other
since we were little,

66
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,360
but I don't love her.

67
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:04,200
You love Ms. Mook, right?

68
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:06,920
Yes.

69
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:13,120
I'm glad you've found
a nice woman like her.

70
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:18,680
But Mrs. Anna really loves you,
and she's raised you well.

71
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:24,040
I understand, Mom.

72
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:29,160
But she's forcing me to marry,
and I don't agree with it.

73
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:31,560
I really can't allow it.

74
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:43,560
It's Mook.

75
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:49,880
- Here, let me help you.
- Thank you.

76
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,760
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

77
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:56,360
Good morning.

78
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:57,760
Good morning.

79
00:06:57,840 --> 00:07:00,200
How are you doing, Ms. Narin?

80
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:01,840
I'm doing a lot better now.

81
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:04,960
The doctor's discharging me in a few days.

82
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:06,240
I really appreciate your help, Ms. Mook.

83
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,840
If you hadn't, I'd be doing way worse.

84
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:16,360
And thank you
for helping me see my son again.

85
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,480
Thank you for helping Saifah
all this time.

86
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:26,680
I haven't really done much for Mr. Thee.

87
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:35,240
Hey, I told my mom that I love you.

88
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:50,480
Hold each other's hands tightly, honey.

89
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:53,880
Deal with your problems one by one.

90
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,560
I'm rooting for you.

91
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,000
My mom likes you.

92
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:24,640
Yeah?

93
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:51,040
So, what should we do now,
about Mrs. Anna?

94
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,600
I'll probably have to give her some time.

95
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:00,960
For now, I want to take care of my mom
until she recovers.

96
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:03,200
Good idea.

97
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:05,680
That way, you'll get to spend
lots of time with her.

98
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:10,760
Mook,

99
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:15,440
I really appreciate you
for telling me to calm down.

100
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:18,040
Otherwise,

101
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:20,480
I would've misunderstood my mom
for the rest of my life.

102
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:29,760
Mook, do you remember?

103
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:33,240
I asked you to have faith in my love.

104
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:37,760
I've proven it to you, see?

105
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,760
Thank you.

106
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,760
I thought what happened to us was crazy,

107
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:16,360
but what happened to Mr. Thee
was somehow crazier!

108
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:20,840
It's a good thing, though,
that he got to see his mother again.

109
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:28,000
He called off the wedding.

110
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,800
That means he chooses you, Mook!

111
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:36,960
But I don't know
how it'll go for us either.

112
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:39,200
Of course, it's going to be
a happy ending.

113
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:41,280
Everything's sorted out now.

114
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,880
You're the one who told me
to deal with my problems, Mook.

115
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,840
I got through the worst thing
that ever happened to me

116
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:56,520
because of you.

117
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,920
Mr. Thee's proven himself.

118
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:02,640
Now it's your turn to help him in return.

119
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,720
I know that.

120
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,480
I'm just scared.

121
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:11,640
I'm scared that it won't work out
like I'm hoping it would.

122
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:15,320
I'm scared that
I'll make my mom sad again.

123
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:20,440
I think she'll understand, though,

124
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:25,440
because she can tell
that you really like Mr. Thee.

125
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:33,680
You've got to fight.

126
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:40,720
Come on, fight!

127
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,040
- Get up!
- Careful!

128
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,560
Us three, the three nasty girls…

129
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:49,400
No, pretty girls.

130
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,040
No matter how much drama comes our way,

131
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:54,200
we won't be afraid of anything, right?

132
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,720
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

133
00:11:58,320 --> 00:11:59,560
Come on, let's recharge.

134
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:02,200
- Thanks.
- We've got this!

135
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,920
Mr. Pun,

136
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,560
please shower and do your homework,

137
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:28,360
or your mother will scold you
when she gets home.

138
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:38,800
Mr. Pun, your mother's home.

139
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:46,320
Why hasn't he showered yet?

140
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,560
Can't you see what time it is?

141
00:12:48,520 --> 00:12:50,480
I've told him many times,

142
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:52,680
but he wouldn't stop playing video games.

143
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:58,800
Pun,

144
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:02,040
stop playing video games,
go shower, and do your homework, okay?

145
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,880
Pun.

146
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,600
I told you to stop playing. Now.

147
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,160
Can't you hear me?

148
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:16,640
I told you to stop right now!

149
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:17,920
I don't want to shower yet.

150
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,160
I want to play video games.

151
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:23,800
Give it back!

152
00:13:23,880 --> 00:13:26,320
I said I want to play video games!

153
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,320
Why'd you take my video game?

154
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:30,080
So you're going against my orders?

155
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:31,800
You order everyone around!

156
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,360
Not just me, but Dad too.

157
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:35,560
And when we don't do what you say,
you fight with us.

158
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:38,160
Who taught you to say that?

159
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:39,400
But it's true!

160
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:42,040
You and Dad always fight
whenever you meet.

161
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:44,040
You're so heartless!

162
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:45,720
I hate you, Mom!

163
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:48,560
Mr. Pun.

164
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,440
Mr. Pun.

165
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:12,880
<i>A kid's behavior can change</i>

166
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:15,440
when they've been exposed to violence,

167
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:21,120
such as raising your voice,
arguing, or fighting,

168
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:24,360
all of which can lead
to behavioral changes in kids.

169
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:30,560
Are you accusing us
of making our son a troubled kid?

170
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:34,240
It helps to stop behaving violently
in front of your kid.

171
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:38,120
I'm counting on you both.

172
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:42,240
<i>We'll have to help each other,</i>
<i>both at school and at home.</i>

173
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:32,720
<i>I want to marry Pat.</i>

174
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,560
I love him, Dad.

175
00:15:35,280 --> 00:15:36,280
Just think it through.

176
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,840
I'm a politician.

177
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:41,040
I've worked in politics all my life,

178
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:44,120
so I want a son-in-law
who can carry on my work.

179
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,840
But I'll marry no one but him.

180
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:52,760
Then, can you convince him
to work with me?

181
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:55,640
He seems to only care
about running his travel agency,

182
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:58,360
and he doesn't have a lot of money either.

183
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:05,720
Don't worry, Dad.

184
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:08,200
I'll make sure he works with you.

185
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:14,360
Pat's a pushover.

186
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,240
He'll do anything I say.

187
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:18,880
But as for his money, I don't care.

188
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:24,000
Well, we have enough
to last a lifetime anyway.

189
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:27,160
Please, Dad.

190
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:29,120
Please let me marry Pat.

191
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:31,920
Please?

192
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,880
Please, Dad?

193
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,640
I warned you, Prao.

194
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:46,160
Just don't regret it later.

195
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:50,280
Thank you!

196
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:01,280
Thank you.

197
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,040
It's our home, Prao.

198
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:09,400
I worked hard to afford this house
for our family.

199
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:11,760
I actually like it here,

200
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:15,720
but if my dad saw it,
he wouldn't let me live here.

201
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:19,960
You know how much he worries about me.

202
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:34,320
Are you all set?

203
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:36,400
Let's go, then. My dad's waiting.

204
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:39,320
But we have to go
to our son's school event today.

205
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:43,560
That's today?

206
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:47,360
But my dad's party
is having an important meeting.

207
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:48,760
We have to be there.

208
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:50,760
Dad wants to introduce you
to his party members.

209
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:54,080
What about our son's school event, Prao?

210
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:56,480
If we don't go see his show, he'll be sad.

211
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,240
Don't overthink it, Pat.

212
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:02,360
Once he's with his friends,
he'll have fun and forget us.

213
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:05,720
Then you can go to your dad's meeting.

214
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:06,920
I'll go to our son's event.

215
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:13,640
Pat!

216
00:18:22,760 --> 00:18:25,480
RUAM JAI PARTY

217
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:26,800
Good afternoon.

218
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:27,960
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

219
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:33,520
Where's your husband?

220
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:37,720
Let me try calling him.

221
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:49,840
Oh, hello, Mr. Pansak.

222
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,440
- Hello, Mr. Siri.
- Hello.

223
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:52,640
- Hello.
- Hello, Ms. Yupa.

224
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:56,120
I heard you're announcing
the new MP candidate today. Where is he?

225
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,640
Bring him over and introduce us.

226
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:05,800
Something urgent came up,
so Pat couldn't come.

227
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:09,280
What a shame. If you'll excuse us.

228
00:19:09,360 --> 00:19:11,240
Sure, Mr. Siri. Go ahead, ma'am.

229
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:21,240
I'm sorry, Dad.

230
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:26,360
You should just accept reality
and let Pat go.

231
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,840
You can never change him.

232
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:33,200
Come on, let's head inside,
Mr. Siri. Let's go.

233
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:35,960
Let's talk inside. We're ready.

234
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:18,080
I had to cancel my event
at the association just to wait for you.

235
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:20,640
Mommy, I want to eat pizza.

236
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:23,080
I can't let you eat junk food.

237
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:25,680
My son has to become successful,
like his grandpa.

238
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:27,640
No one wants to be your puppet, Prao.

239
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:33,600
I'll get to play
in the water now, right, Mommy?

240
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:35,560
Where have you been?

241
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:37,960
You know you upset my dad, right?

242
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:40,920
- Because you're--
- Let's talk later.

243
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:43,120
We're here to take our son
on a trip, remember?

244
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,040
Then you can take him.

245
00:20:45,120 --> 00:20:46,560
I'm not in the mood.

246
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:53,640
You two are yelling at each other again.

247
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:09,800
<i>The problem is that you never trust me.</i>

248
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:13,000
You never listened to me

249
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:15,640
or agreed with anything I said.

250
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:19,880
You just want me to be
what you want me to be.

251
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:25,400
You should ask yourself
if you still even want me, Prao.

252
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,160
I won.

253
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:24,880
Congratulations.

254
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:30,600
Just how many awards have you won
since the day we met?

255
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:33,480
Thank you

256
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:37,200
for always supporting me
and rooting for me.

257
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:45,880
I wish my dad was as supportive as you.

258
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:49,080
Have you spoken to your dad at all?

259
00:22:54,080 --> 00:22:56,520
He rarely cares about me anyway.

260
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:58,040
And after that thing with Thee,

261
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:02,400
it looks like I'll have to stay
in Thailand permanently

262
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:04,040
because he won't let me return.

263
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:05,840
Are you okay?

264
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,520
Let's celebrate somewhere.

265
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,400
{\an8}PRAO

266
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:23,160
Go right ahead.

267
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:36,200
Yes, Prao?

268
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:39,760
What?

269
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:41,960
You want me to pick up our son?

270
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:51,800
You should go.

271
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:54,000
We can celebrate some other day.

272
00:23:54,080 --> 00:23:55,760
I've got work to do anyway.

273
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:36,160
I love eating pizza here the most, Mommy.

274
00:24:38,240 --> 00:24:40,240
If you like it, then don't hold back.

275
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:53,720
Can I really eat pizza, Mommy?

276
00:24:57,280 --> 00:24:59,160
Of course you can. You have my permission.

277
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:00,960
Okay?

278
00:25:04,960 --> 00:25:06,400
- Is it good?
- Yes.

279
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:12,560
Are you happy today?

280
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:16,040
See, I'm not fighting
with your dad at all.

281
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:29,800
Then,

282
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:31,800
if…

283
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:37,200
your dad and I were to become friends
and not fight again,

284
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:39,720
would you like that?

285
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:44,080
If you were friends, you wouldn't fight,

286
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:49,520
just like how
Kongkwan and I don't fight, right?

287
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,160
Yes.

288
00:26:00,040 --> 00:26:02,160
- Eat up, okay?
- Okay.

289
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:03,560
Want anything else? I'll get it for you.

290
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:06,160
Which topping do you want? This one?

291
00:26:08,920 --> 00:26:10,280
Eat up, okay?

292
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:35,840
Let's go.

293
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:42,160
Go upstairs, take a shower,
and do your homework, Pun.

294
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,440
Okay.

295
00:26:44,840 --> 00:26:46,280
See you later, Daddy.

296
00:26:46,360 --> 00:26:47,520
See you later.

297
00:26:48,360 --> 00:26:49,200
Come on.

298
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:57,280
Come on in.

299
00:26:57,360 --> 00:26:58,560
We need to talk.

300
00:27:16,560 --> 00:27:18,480
When are you going to see my dad?

301
00:27:22,520 --> 00:27:26,040
Prao, you already know
that I'll never enter politics.

302
00:27:27,760 --> 00:27:29,760
I've always told you that, haven't I?

303
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:35,120
Actually, I always knew the answer.

304
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:39,800
I just chose to lie to myself.

305
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:45,440
Ever since the day we got married,

306
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:48,240
I thought

307
00:27:49,840 --> 00:27:51,840
I could change your mind one day.

308
00:27:57,360 --> 00:28:01,800
If there were just the two of us,
I'd keep on fighting.

309
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:04,880
But we have a child now,

310
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:08,600
and I don't want him
to witness our problems anymore.

311
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:14,680
Now I understand
just how badly our problems affected him.

312
00:28:19,520 --> 00:28:21,680
I've been keeping tabs on you

313
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:24,640
because I didn't want anyone
to take what's mine.

314
00:28:31,280 --> 00:28:34,160
But now, I don't need to try
and keep you anymore.

315
00:28:38,560 --> 00:28:40,920
It's better to break up
when we can still talk

316
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:45,320
than to end up hating each other.

317
00:28:55,720 --> 00:28:58,360
But what about our son, Prao?

318
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:01,000
What are you going to do?

319
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:08,280
Today, I saw him being happy.

320
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:14,960
It means that
if we stopped being husband and wife,

321
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:17,920
stopped fighting, and stopped arguing,

322
00:29:19,600 --> 00:29:21,880
we'd become parents with a united front.

323
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:27,000
Maybe then, our son might
be happier than how he is now.

324
00:29:29,880 --> 00:29:32,240
I don't want to hurt him anymore.

325
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:47,240
I agree with you.

326
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:52,240
And I must apologize to you too.

327
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:55,160
I can't be who you hoped I'd be.

328
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:03,520
It's not your fault.

329
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:07,680
I was the one
who chose this in the first place.

330
00:30:53,960 --> 00:30:57,480
Thank you, Teacher,
for saving my son's life.

331
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:04,480
Saifah was a very good kid.

332
00:31:05,240 --> 00:31:08,520
Although he wasn't here for long,
I could sense that he's a good person.

333
00:31:10,280 --> 00:31:12,000
Congratulations.

334
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:13,680
Thank you, Teacher.

335
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:17,720
Even after he moved out of here,

336
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:20,680
he's always helped the kids
at Piamsuk Orphanage.

337
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:25,800
Many kids here got to go to school
thanks to his donations.

338
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:28,200
I'm glad I could help out.

339
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:33,800
So, does Mrs. Anna know about this yet?

340
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:43,680
Please give her some time.

341
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:47,120
She adopted you
when you were little, after all.

342
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:51,040
Maybe now that you've found
your real mother,

343
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:54,400
Mrs. Anna doesn't quite know how to act.

344
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:56,800
Sure.

345
00:31:57,320 --> 00:31:58,200
Sure.

346
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:01,000
I'll try to help her understand.

347
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:03,760
I hope she'll listen to me.

348
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:22,640
You were lucky

349
00:32:22,720 --> 00:32:25,440
to have found this place
in your toughest times.

350
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:31,800
Let's not mention it ever again, Mom.

351
00:32:33,440 --> 00:32:36,480
I'm glad to meet you again.

352
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:41,520
I'm glad to meet you too, Thee.

353
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:48,640
I want to offer a scholarship
for the children here too.

354
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:04,400
How about we name it Saengtawan?

355
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:29,200
I found out about Tawan.

356
00:33:36,040 --> 00:33:38,720
PIAMSUK ORPHANAGE

357
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:56,840
Saifah sure is lucky
to meet his real mother.

358
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:59,960
You know, I felt really sorry
for him back then.

359
00:34:01,120 --> 00:34:02,680
His home was on fire,

360
00:34:02,760 --> 00:34:07,360
and his brother
was burned to death in front of him.

361
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:11,639
I'm sorry?

362
00:34:12,280 --> 00:34:15,199
I heard some locals saved Saifah,

363
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:19,800
but his brother passed away in the fire.

364
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:35,080
Mom.

365
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:44,560
Mom, I'm sorry…

366
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:49,600
that I wasn't upfront with you.

367
00:34:52,040 --> 00:34:56,400
I was afraid that if I told you,
your condition would get worse.

368
00:35:02,680 --> 00:35:04,120
It's okay, honey.

369
00:35:04,840 --> 00:35:07,400
You don't have to apologize. I understand.

370
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:19,960
At least in all this misfortune,
there's something good too.

371
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:24,600
Just to see you today

372
00:35:26,200 --> 00:35:30,480
is such a great gift for me, honey.

373
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:46,320
I want to offer a scholarship
for all the disadvantaged children.

374
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:48,880
I'm sure your brother would be happy.

375
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:54,080
Sure, Mom.

376
00:35:56,200 --> 00:35:57,800
If Tawan were still alive,

377
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:03,040
he'd be happy to hear.

378
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:27,520
Thee,

379
00:36:28,240 --> 00:36:30,480
there's one more person I want to meet.

380
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:36,640
Who, Mom?

381
00:36:48,720 --> 00:36:49,920
Go to sleep, honey.

382
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:55,080
Mommy, when will you
invite Thee over again?

383
00:36:55,160 --> 00:36:56,800
I miss him.

384
00:36:58,440 --> 00:37:00,360
You like him a lot, don't you, Kongkwan?

385
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:02,880
I do. He's fun to talk to.

386
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:06,840
He likes to play with me,
and he's kind too.

387
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:13,560
I'll remember to tell him
that you miss him.

388
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:15,720
Okay.

389
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:18,800
Go to sleep, okay?

390
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:38,080
It's been a long time since I had
such a good banana in coconut milk.

391
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:40,680
Please, dig in, Ms. Narin.

392
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:42,800
Thank you.

393
00:37:48,720 --> 00:37:51,080
Aren't you going to try some, Mr. Thee?

394
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:52,840
Sure.

395
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:03,240
Mook already told me
about you and Mr. Thee.

396
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:04,840
I'm really happy for you.

397
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:09,160
I really appreciate that.

398
00:38:09,240 --> 00:38:11,880
It might just be the best thing
that's ever happened to me.

399
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:15,080
And I must thank Mook, too,

400
00:38:15,160 --> 00:38:18,800
for helping me and my son
understand each other better.

401
00:38:27,760 --> 00:38:30,000
Take off your shoes, okay? Good job, honey

402
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:31,800
Thee!

403
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:33,960
- Hello.
- Hello.

404
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:35,680
- Hello.
- I'm back.

405
00:38:35,760 --> 00:38:38,480
- Hello, Auntie.
- Hello.

406
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:41,120
Are you here to see me?

407
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:42,680
I really miss you, Thee.

408
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:44,080
Yes, I am.

409
00:38:45,160 --> 00:38:47,120
I have a new toy to show you.

410
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:48,040
Come and see.

411
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:50,240
Right now?

412
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:54,040
- Then, I'll be right back.
- Okay.

413
00:38:54,800 --> 00:38:56,240
Kongkwan.

414
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:58,440
Then, I'd better go look after her.

415
00:38:59,320 --> 00:39:00,160
Go right ahead.

416
00:39:05,200 --> 00:39:07,440
Kongkwan always gets that way
when she meets Mr. Thee.

417
00:39:08,680 --> 00:39:09,520
I see.

418
00:39:13,280 --> 00:39:15,040
I wanted to apologize on my son's behalf

419
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:17,640
for all the things he's done
to make Mook sad.

420
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:21,600
I was never mad at him.

421
00:39:22,200 --> 00:39:23,320
I just felt bad for my daughter.

422
00:39:24,640 --> 00:39:26,880
Mook's been let down
by this kind of problem before.

423
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:30,800
I don't want my daughter
to get hurt by the same problems again.

424
00:39:33,840 --> 00:39:35,200
I understand.

425
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:38,560
To mothers like us,
our child's happiness matters the most.

426
00:39:40,040 --> 00:39:44,120
But Thee's proven
just how serious he is about Mook.

427
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:48,360
You may have heard
that he refused to get married.

428
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:56,040
I understand
that you're worried about Mook.

429
00:39:57,720 --> 00:40:00,080
But I think those two
really love each other.

430
00:40:01,560 --> 00:40:02,840
I believe

431
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:06,360
that they'll be ready to fight
through any obstacles that may come.

432
00:40:07,680 --> 00:40:10,000
I hope you'll give Thee a chance.

433
00:40:17,680 --> 00:40:19,160
I should dig in.

434
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:24,560
- This one.
- A seat for Mommy.

435
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:26,480
It should be back there.

436
00:40:26,560 --> 00:40:28,760
- Oh yeah?
- Because this one…

437
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:34,560
Won't you come help us build?

438
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:36,800
Sure.

439
00:40:38,960 --> 00:40:40,160
Let's see.

440
00:40:40,240 --> 00:40:41,640
What are you building here?

441
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:44,640
We're building a house, Mommy.

442
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:46,760
Thee said

443
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:50,040
if we want to build a strong house,
we have to work together.

444
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:58,000
You have to help too,
so our house will be perfect.

445
00:41:02,240 --> 00:41:03,600
I'll build our house

446
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:06,440
and our family.

447
00:41:07,960 --> 00:41:09,600
But I can't do it alone.

448
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:11,920
You have to help me.

449
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:27,000
Sure.

450
00:41:27,840 --> 00:41:29,680
We'll build a house together.

451
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:37,200
Okay.

452
00:41:38,080 --> 00:41:39,200
Here, right?

453
00:41:40,720 --> 00:41:41,920
Yes.

454
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:43,920
Now we've got all three.

455
00:41:44,440 --> 00:41:45,400
Who's this?

456
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:46,440
You.

457
00:41:46,520 --> 00:41:47,880
- What about this?
- Mommy.

458
00:41:47,960 --> 00:41:49,680
- And who's this?
- Me.

459
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:53,320
Why'd you make me mow the lawn?

460
00:41:53,400 --> 00:41:54,720
Because that's your job.

461
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:59,080
So I need to mow the lawn
in order to live here?

462
00:42:31,360 --> 00:42:33,240
I've given them the envelope.

463
00:42:33,840 --> 00:42:37,520
Usa, what if we get caught
rigging the bid with Mr. Somkiat?

464
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:40,720
And what if our company actually wins?

465
00:42:41,400 --> 00:42:42,800
Where will we get the funding?

466
00:42:44,200 --> 00:42:46,240
Don't be afraid of such nonsense, Kuk.

467
00:42:46,320 --> 00:42:49,120
I told you, Mrs. Anna
will fully support us.

468
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:52,720
As for the funding,
she'll take care of it too.

469
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:55,360
All we need to do is win the bid.

470
00:43:01,240 --> 00:43:04,320
I'll help you any way I can.

471
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:07,080
I won't leave you like Mook did.

472
00:43:22,040 --> 00:43:24,480
I'm treating you
to many fancy Chinese dishes today

473
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:27,440
to celebrate the good news
our family is getting.

474
00:43:28,240 --> 00:43:29,720
What good news, Ma?

475
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:33,800
The good news about your company's
big project, of course.

476
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:38,840
Once the official result
has been announced,

477
00:43:38,920 --> 00:43:42,400
Kuk and I will treat you to a meal
at the most expensive restaurant.

478
00:43:42,480 --> 00:43:44,440
You're such a great girlfriend, Usa.

479
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:49,800
I'm just glad there's no black shadow
to bring bad luck into our house.

480
00:43:49,880 --> 00:43:51,640
Ever since Mook left,

481
00:43:51,720 --> 00:43:55,160
our house has been filled
with good energy and good news.

482
00:43:56,360 --> 00:43:59,680
Well, she's now a dark shadow
at A Round Trip instead, Ma.

483
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:01,640
Mrs. Anna got so upset

484
00:44:01,720 --> 00:44:03,960
that she wanted to end their contract.

485
00:44:05,360 --> 00:44:07,960
Soon, we'll get to replace them for sure.

486
00:44:09,760 --> 00:44:11,120
Do you believe me now?

487
00:44:11,200 --> 00:44:14,120
A dragon will always be a dragon.

488
00:44:14,200 --> 00:44:17,040
There's no way you will lose
to a girl like Mook.

489
00:44:17,120 --> 00:44:18,280
I'm sure of that.

490
00:44:20,400 --> 00:44:21,400
Sure, Ma.

491
00:44:22,600 --> 00:44:25,560
Right, eat up. Don't hold back.

492
00:44:27,480 --> 00:44:28,640
Some chicken for your health.

493
00:44:28,720 --> 00:44:29,760
- Thank you.
- There.

494
00:44:30,320 --> 00:44:32,520
- Give some to Usa too.
- Eat up, okay?

495
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:33,840
Good.

496
00:44:34,760 --> 00:44:36,160
Eat up.

497
00:44:53,760 --> 00:44:55,600
So the troublemaker's asleep?

498
00:44:56,280 --> 00:44:57,760
Yes, Mom.

499
00:44:57,840 --> 00:44:59,640
She must be tired after playing all day.

500
00:45:03,640 --> 00:45:06,840
Today, Ms. Narin apologized to me
on Mr. Thee's behalf.

501
00:45:10,600 --> 00:45:12,080
How is he doing, by the way?

502
00:45:14,320 --> 00:45:16,320
Mrs. Anna is really angry.

503
00:45:16,400 --> 00:45:18,360
She removed him from his CEO position,

504
00:45:19,280 --> 00:45:22,000
so now Mr. Thee has more time
to look after Ms. Narin.

505
00:45:24,080 --> 00:45:26,360
Maybe it's better this way.

506
00:45:29,400 --> 00:45:31,760
I'm not sure about that.

507
00:45:35,680 --> 00:45:37,560
It's up to you now.

508
00:45:38,400 --> 00:45:42,800
Are you ready to go back to him?

509
00:45:49,080 --> 00:45:50,440
Do you think

510
00:45:52,520 --> 00:45:54,200
I'll be let down again?

511
00:45:58,840 --> 00:46:01,200
No one knows the future, Mook.

512
00:46:02,280 --> 00:46:03,800
You just need to be prepared.

513
00:46:04,520 --> 00:46:06,120
And you have to ask yourself

514
00:46:06,200 --> 00:46:09,880
if you're ready to start over.

515
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:17,640
You're not mad at him anymore, right?

516
00:46:21,520 --> 00:46:22,600
I wasn't.

517
00:46:24,760 --> 00:46:26,800
I just didn't want to see you get hurt.

518
00:46:29,040 --> 00:46:33,320
But Mr. Thee's proven to me
that he'd give up anything for you.

519
00:46:35,600 --> 00:46:40,760
All there's left to do is to ask yourself
what your decision will be.

520
00:47:15,120 --> 00:47:16,520
Why'd you come back?

521
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:17,680
Did you forget something?

522
00:47:19,600 --> 00:47:21,200
I forgot…

523
00:47:22,640 --> 00:47:24,760
What is it?
Tell me, so I can get it for you.

524
00:47:31,120 --> 00:47:34,280
I forgot whether I've told you
that I love you.

525
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:38,520
You already did.

526
00:47:39,960 --> 00:47:43,080
You did that day. Don't you remember?

527
00:47:48,840 --> 00:47:50,400
I meant today.

528
00:47:53,960 --> 00:47:55,360
I want to tell you every day.

529
00:48:01,040 --> 00:48:02,560
I love you, Mook.

530
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:09,280
Mook?

531
00:48:18,120 --> 00:48:19,720
I love you too.

532
00:48:21,440 --> 00:48:22,280
That's all I needed.

533
00:49:03,000 --> 00:49:04,240
CALLING…

534
00:49:23,480 --> 00:49:24,800
Where is he?

535
00:49:39,880 --> 00:49:41,320
I'm friends with Ms. Bell.

536
00:49:46,680 --> 00:49:48,200
And I'm also friends with Mr. Thee.

537
00:49:49,640 --> 00:49:52,600
I heard from Mr. Thee
that you have business here,

538
00:49:53,200 --> 00:49:54,680
so I wanted to see you.

539
00:49:58,360 --> 00:49:59,680
What is it?

540
00:50:18,320 --> 00:50:22,160
This is an award Ms. Bell won
in a contest for designers.

541
00:50:25,680 --> 00:50:28,800
I think the person
she wants to show it off to the most

542
00:50:28,880 --> 00:50:30,240
is you.

543
00:50:35,520 --> 00:50:40,200
Ms. Bell's worked hard to prove herself
so that you'd see her worth.

544
00:50:41,720 --> 00:50:45,320
That's more important to her
than the award itself.

545
00:50:49,160 --> 00:50:52,560
If you're here to talk about this,
you shouldn't bother.

546
00:50:54,080 --> 00:50:55,080
You should leave.

547
00:51:18,120 --> 00:51:21,040
Our bookings have dropped significantly,

548
00:51:21,640 --> 00:51:24,480
perhaps because we don't have
a campaign to boost our sales.

549
00:51:25,120 --> 00:51:26,480
Then why don't we launch one?

550
00:51:26,560 --> 00:51:28,760
The campaign Mr. Thee worked on
was about to be launched,

551
00:51:28,840 --> 00:51:30,480
but I see we still haven't promoted it.

552
00:51:31,360 --> 00:51:33,840
So, are we promoting the couple campaign,

553
00:51:33,920 --> 00:51:35,000
or are we changing it?

554
00:51:38,080 --> 00:51:40,840
As for the reservation system
and the deals we offer,

555
00:51:40,920 --> 00:51:42,920
Mr. Thee came up with a plan
to adjust the deals,

556
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:45,520
yet right now,
we're still using the old plan.

557
00:51:46,280 --> 00:51:47,440
So, are we changing or not?

558
00:51:48,800 --> 00:51:50,680
If you have any concerns,
leave it with Pitak.

559
00:51:51,720 --> 00:51:52,960
Then we'll find a conclusion.

560
00:51:53,040 --> 00:51:54,840
That's all for today.

561
00:52:09,800 --> 00:52:11,640
What's with all this mess?

562
00:52:12,520 --> 00:52:14,960
So no one can handle anything
at this hotel

563
00:52:15,040 --> 00:52:16,600
just because Thee's gone?

564
00:52:16,680 --> 00:52:17,880
Yes.

565
00:52:18,720 --> 00:52:22,320
Normally, Mr. Thee handles
and decides everything.

566
00:52:47,640 --> 00:52:49,960
How can I work
if you're sitting there staring at me?

567
00:52:50,040 --> 00:52:51,920
It's not like I'm bothering you.

568
00:52:52,560 --> 00:52:54,200
I'm just staring at my girlfriend.

569
00:52:57,480 --> 00:52:59,000
What about Ms. Narin?

570
00:52:59,080 --> 00:53:00,640
Don't you have to be with her?

571
00:53:01,400 --> 00:53:02,800
You can call her Mom.

572
00:53:09,200 --> 00:53:11,160
Is Mom doing better now?

573
00:53:11,240 --> 00:53:14,200
Yes. She's gone back to work today.

574
00:53:14,720 --> 00:53:16,560
She must be worried about her staff there.

575
00:53:18,840 --> 00:53:21,280
She loves all of her employees
like they're family.

576
00:53:21,800 --> 00:53:23,800
Everyone must be happy she's back to work.

577
00:53:27,960 --> 00:53:29,800
Anyway, give me a second.

578
00:53:29,880 --> 00:53:31,240
I'll be done with work in a bit.

579
00:53:32,120 --> 00:53:34,000
Take your time. No rush.

580
00:53:34,080 --> 00:53:35,600
I have to meet someone today anyway.

581
00:53:35,680 --> 00:53:36,760
Okay.

582
00:53:47,720 --> 00:53:49,800
Mr. Thee, someone's here to see you.

583
00:53:55,440 --> 00:53:57,720
Are you sure you won't return to The One?

584
00:53:57,800 --> 00:54:00,440
It's a mess there right now.

585
00:54:04,600 --> 00:54:06,600
I wasn't the one who wanted to quit.

586
00:54:06,680 --> 00:54:08,160
You know that, Mr. Pitak.

587
00:54:09,840 --> 00:54:12,000
I just can't help but worry.

588
00:54:12,640 --> 00:54:14,720
You know, sometimes I think

589
00:54:14,800 --> 00:54:18,400
you and Mrs. Anna are exactly the same.

590
00:54:18,480 --> 00:54:19,520
How so?

591
00:54:20,320 --> 00:54:22,120
You just don't know how to lose.

592
00:54:24,160 --> 00:54:25,000
Can I see?

593
00:54:25,080 --> 00:54:26,880
What are the problems? I'll take a look.

594
00:54:48,800 --> 00:54:50,440
Are you doing alright now, Ms. Narin?

595
00:54:50,520 --> 00:54:53,560
When we heard that you got sick,
we were so worried.

596
00:54:54,280 --> 00:54:56,120
I'm doing better now. Thank you so much.

597
00:54:56,200 --> 00:54:57,120
You can go back to work.

598
00:54:57,200 --> 00:54:58,200
Okay.

599
00:55:01,200 --> 00:55:03,720
Ms. Narin, I was just looking for you.

600
00:55:04,400 --> 00:55:05,960
What's wrong, Mr. Chadchai?

601
00:55:06,040 --> 00:55:09,440
The One has called
an urgent shareholders' meeting.

602
00:55:17,040 --> 00:55:19,240
Are you sure you don't want
to join us at lunch?

603
00:55:19,840 --> 00:55:21,160
It's okay, Ms. Mook.

604
00:55:21,240 --> 00:55:22,400
I have to rush off to The One,

605
00:55:22,480 --> 00:55:26,960
because ever since Mr. Thee left,
it's so chaotic over there.

606
00:55:28,760 --> 00:55:29,840
Let's go.

607
00:55:32,600 --> 00:55:34,720
K. ANNA

608
00:55:36,160 --> 00:55:37,640
I'm sorry, what?!

609
00:55:42,800 --> 00:55:44,480
Mrs. Anna is at Narin Beach Resort.

610
00:55:44,560 --> 00:55:47,120
She called an urgent meeting
with all executives and teams.

611
00:55:50,840 --> 00:55:51,880
Excuse me for being late.

612
00:55:51,960 --> 00:55:53,760
I didn't know there was an urgent meeting.

613
00:55:55,040 --> 00:55:57,080
I had to call this urgent meeting

614
00:55:57,160 --> 00:56:00,280
because I have something important
to notify you about.

615
00:56:01,680 --> 00:56:04,120
First, please allow me
to introduce myself.

616
00:56:04,800 --> 00:56:07,720
My name is Anna Teerasu.

617
00:56:07,800 --> 00:56:11,040
I am the CEO at TJ Group.

618
00:56:12,360 --> 00:56:13,200
CEO?

619
00:56:16,640 --> 00:56:18,520
Oh dear.

620
00:56:19,040 --> 00:56:21,000
I'm in the wrong seat, aren't I?

621
00:56:21,600 --> 00:56:23,400
No worries. Please have a seat.

622
00:56:29,840 --> 00:56:32,760
{\an8}I'd like to buy back
all of Narin Beach Resort's shares

623
00:56:32,840 --> 00:56:33,760
{\an8}from The One.

624
00:56:38,960 --> 00:56:40,280
{\an8}Prao and I

625
00:56:41,840 --> 00:56:43,400
{\an8}have got divorced.

626
00:56:56,000 --> 00:56:58,360
{\an8}Please take good care of Saifah
for me, Mook.

627
00:56:59,720 --> 00:57:00,600
{\an8}I will.

628
00:57:05,040 --> 00:57:06,160
{\an8}Come here.

629
00:58:04,840 --> 00:58:07,120
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

